description:
The provision for parliamentary scrutiny of each instrument varied, and a handful were laid but subject to no formal scrutiny:

•  293 were made subject to the negative resolution procedure. By convention, instruments subject to the negative resolution procedure are laid before Parliament 21 days before they come into force. However, 173 of them breached that conventional rule;

•  99 have been subject to the made-affirmative procedure;

•  24 have been subject to the draft affirmative procedure.
[Part II.C].
